{"type":"message","id":"71c8c95e","parentId":"f61322bb","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:47:49.566Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the issue is: since the 4.14 update, ALL responses became slow - not just the first message after /new, but every round. This is more serious.\n\nLet me think about what could cause every response to be slower:\n\n1. The v8 scorer/classifier (3103/3105) - if these are now being called on every message and they're slow, that would explain it\n2. The ephemeral logging on every message\n3. Bootstrap files loading on every message\n4. Memory search on every message\n5. Some new hook that's running synchronously\n\nLooking at the SOUL.md v10.1 structure - it now has:\n- 强制显式思考（每次必跑）- The thinking block with 4 sub-sections that must be included in EVERY response\n\n\n- This was a change from the previous version\n\nWait - the thinking block is now MANDATORY for every response. That means every single reply needs to go through the full 4-part thinking process before being output. If this is being done server-side with LLM inference, it would effectively double the generation time for every response since we're essentially doing a thought process first, then the actual response.\n\nBut the user said this is a webchat regression that started on 4.14, so the issue is likely in the bootstrap or memory loading process that runs at the start of each session.\n\nLooking at the startup flow, I run session-summary scan, memory files for today and yesterday, then SOUL.md and USER.md, and session context from context.json. If any of these file reads are hanging or slow, it would delay the entire first response. But if this is happening on every message, not just the first one, then something else is loading repeatedly.\n\nWait - if thinking is set to \"adaptive\" and that's causing slower responses on every message since 4.14, that could be it. The user is experiencing slowdowns on all responses after the 4.14 update, so something changed then. Let me think about what the actual causes could be - maybe the thinking block itself is being processed as part of the response, or there's something in the startup sequence that's now running on every message instead of just once.\n\nI should ask the user to check `/status` to see what's actually running and where the time is being spent.","thinkingSignature":"e90b3b73b83d967145fc876064f48d520da5fc3f36ccf24ca6a3d0186c15d7dd"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n每次都慢 = 不是 session 初始化问题，是处理链路里某个环节在每轮都卡。\n\n最可疑的是 `thinking: adaptive` — 4.14 之前你没动过这个配置的话，回来查一下：\n\n```\n/status\n```\n\n把输出发我，我看看 model 和 thinking 设置。另外你知道 4.14 之后动过哪些配置吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":156,"output":551,"cacheRead":24704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25411,"cost":{"input":0.0000468,"output":0.0006611999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00148224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0021902399999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776343656061,"responseId":"06300d679716ee3a7d220c3a2f744122"}}
