{"type":"message","id":"a9c23101","parentId":"c8dc0251","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:48:44.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is telling me to be more proactive and figure it out myself. Let me think about what could cause universal slowdown after a 4.14 update.\n\nLooking at MEMORY.md, I can see the framework architecture. The v8 微服务 stack includes:\n- 3103 Scorer (port 3103)\n- 3105 Classifier v2 (port 3105)\n- 3102 v8-Router (port 3102)\n\nEvery message goes through these classifiers before the AI generates a response. If any of these services are slow or hanging, it would affect every single turn.\n\nLet me check the status of these services. I should run some diagnostic commands to check if any of the v8 services are having issues.\n\nAlso, thinking about what changed on 4.14:\n\n\n- The SOUL.md was restructured to v10.1\n- Bootstrap hooks were fixed\n- Session summary hook was fixed\n\nBut these are all file/guidance changes, not runtime service changes. The slowdown being universal across all messages suggests a service-level issue rather than something specific to my prompts or guidance files.\n\nI should check if the v8 scorer/classifier endpoints are responsive, and look at what's actually running on ports 3102, 3103, and 3105.","thinkingSignature":"f6841ccf0d7f2075b19c25eb0a1a1971e7cf01c2736e540f4131127660ccf03e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，我直接查。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6ab77f3e9cb643e99ea8991f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -w \"\\n%{http_code} %{time_total}s\" http://localhost:3103/api/score -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"test\",\"history\":[]}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"3103 DOWN\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f2310f18326944d0af45077f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -w \"\\n%{http_code} %{time_total}s\" http://localhost:3105/classify -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"test\",\"history\":[]}' 2>/dev/null 