{"type":"message","id":"8da51c35","parentId":"bb29514d","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:49:01.131Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key observations:\n1. 3103 scorer: 200 in 0.001774s - super fast, fine\n2. 3105 classifier: 200 in 0.134127s - a bit slow (134ms) but not terrible\n3. openclaw-gateway is running (PID 503055), using 13.1% CPU and 3.3% memory, running for about 1 hour 50 minutes (20:34 uptime)\n\nThe gateway process looks normal. But I notice `openclaw-listener` is also running (PID 577). There are two processes:\n- openclaw-listener (PID 577) - from `/home/ai/openclaw-listener/dist/main.js`\n\n\n- openclaw-gateway (PID 503055) - the main gateway\n\nBoth are active, which seems odd. The user's concern is that responses got slower after the April 14th framework changes, so I should check what changed in SOUL.md v10.1 around that time that might be impacting performance.\n\nThe thinking block requirement adds processing overhead, but more likely is that bootstrap now loads session-summary files and daily memory on every /new. I need to verify whether these files are being injected into the context properly.\n\nI'm also noticing two processes running simultaneously—`openclaw-listener` and `openclaw-gateway`—which could be causing resource contention if they're both trying to handle requests. Let me get the current status to see what's actually configured and where the bottleneck might be.","thinkingSignature":"d58863605c2ea342a90a113817d5924fd769c5f250078bc5a4cba45dafc4fe92"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6cc8415f3c624eeeaf171bb7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw && cat config.yaml 2>/dev/null | head -60 || cat config.json 2>/dev/null | head -60"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4bac3e7efcde4bf0bdb9ccea","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>/dev/null || echo \"CLI not available\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2202,"output":3