{"type":"message","id":"73d7b32f","parentId":"41c4f3dd","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:49:28.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw.log shows the v8.0 scorer running fine - it's been up since Apr 15 04:40:50. That's not the issue.\n\nThe problem must be something in the agent's processing chain. Let me think about what changed on Apr 14 that could cause slow responses.\n\nLooking at the session - this is running with `model=minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` and `thinking=adaptive`. The user says responses are slow since Apr 14.\n\nOne thing I notice: the 3105 classifier took 0.134s which is a bit slow. And the session was started at 20:41 but the last log entry is from Apr 15. \n\n\nI should check the gateway process itself - it's consuming 13.1% CPU and 620MB of memory, which is substantial. There might be something happening within the current session that's causing the slowdown. Let me look at what's actually running in the session right now rather than digging through old logs.","thinkingSignature":"342a551dcba5fd1bfe191979b98fb54c3ccd50848e47c298799ce8f7c3e27b0f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nscorer 和 classifier 都在线，没问题。gateway 进程 (PID 503055) CPU 13.1%、内存 620MB——偏高，但不一定是病因。\n\n看看当前 session 的实时状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_be7dad6fce5449848be3a77c","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"activeMinutes":120,"limit":5,"messageLimit":3}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2971be63d5bd434f98105730","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -lt ~/.openclaw/sessions/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8188,"output":330,"cacheRead":29568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38086,"cost":{"input":0.0024564,"output":0.000396,"cacheRead":0.00177408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0046264800000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776343759141,"responseId":"06300dcd960eabb13b03ea5946d45dc3"}}
