{"type":"message","id":"c08b03bd","parentId":"ee66a81a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:55:14.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying that the issue is about messages they SEND taking time to appear on screen - not about my response time. This is a **message sending delay on their end**, not a processing delay.\n\nThis is 100% a webchat UI / polling mechanism issue. When they type a message and hit send, it takes time for that message to actually appear in the webchat interface. This is not about my LLM processing at all.\n\nThis is the send-side delay they mentioned earlier (\"我发出去的信息需要等时机才会显示\"). They initially said \"什么情况\" and I told them it was channel polling. Then they said \"你放屁我更新前都没有这种情况\". So this is definitely a regression.\n \nSo the distinction is clear: they send a message, but it doesn't show up in the UI immediately - there's a delay before their own message appears on screen. This is purely a webchat sender-side issue, not something on the processing side. I initially thought it might be the channel polling delay I mentioned, but they're saying this never happened before the update, so something in the webchat UI must have changed. I see the distinction now—the user is saying their sent messages aren't appearing on screen at all, not just delayed, which suggests the send action itself is failing rather than just slow. This points to either the webchat plugin's send mechanism failing silently, or perhaps the UI is using a pending state that never resolves. The fact that they mentioned something was working fine before the update makes me think the issue is in the plugin's message handling logic rather than a normal async delay. The distinction is becoming clearer—they're distinguishing between send delays and processing delays, which suggests these are separate issues. Since they're using webchat and not Signal, the real question is what actually changed in the webchat plugin between versions. Rather than speculating further, I should ask them to test sending a simple message right now to see if it appears immediately or if there's a delay, so I can determine if this is an active send issue or a pre-existing condition they hadn't noticed before. The distinction they're making is that before the update, their sent messages appeared instantly in the UI, but now there's a delay—and my responses also come through slowly due to the polling mechanism. So there are actually two separate issues: the send-side delay and the receive-side polling lag, both of which started after the 4.14 update.","thinkingSignature":"ff4e24d6b6cd1926199dd1350aca8619b947be62dab8729f171c2d991fff147f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了，是两个独立问题：\n\n1. **你发的消息显示慢** — 发送端延迟（这次 /new 之前就有的问题）\n2. **我的回复慢** — 接收端 polling 延迟（4.14 之后变慢）\n\n之前你说是\"更新后全都变慢了\"，现在确认是两个问题。发送端我可以查 webchat 插件的代码。接收端（polling 间隔）也可以查。\n\n先查发送端：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_54683f9dcce54679a1f614ec","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/extensions/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e6ee2a9d77014139b390bdf9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/extensions/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1031,"output":680,"cacheRead":44224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45935,"cost":{"input":0.0003093,"output":0.000816,"cacheRead":0.00265344,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00377874}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344098413,"responseId":"06300f211a134a86634c7e58693ea087"}}
