{"type":"message","id":"443f2731","parentId":"3862efc4","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:55:46.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The listener has a messageHandler.ts and queue.ts. These likely handle incoming and outgoing messages. Let me look at these files to understand the polling mechanism for webchat.\n\nBut wait - the listener is a separate process from the gateway. The webchat channel might work differently. Let me look at the listener's main.ts to understand the architecture.\n\nActually, let me step back and think about this differently. The user says messages they send take time to appear on screen. This is the classic \"message polling delay\" problem. The question is whether this delay changed after 4.14.\n\nLet me check the listener's messageHandler to see how messages are received and sent.","thinkingSignature":"d395142b1d3faaf260d29813a861c918ca166d5a631061e878205566edb4d9fb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3a17e21bff774e3197cab4c8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/openclaw-listener/src/messageHandler.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":283,"output":171,"cacheRead":46208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46662,"cost":{"input":0.00008489999999999999,"output":0.0002052,"cacheRead":0.00277248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00306258}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344138880,"responseId":"06300f49d8325da811671a76dd78a068"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1cbaec1e","parentId":"443f2731","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:55:46.716Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3a17e21bff774e3197cab4c8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { GatewayClient } from './gatewayClient';\nimport { ApiClient } from './apiClient';\nimport { MessageQueue } from './queue';\nimport { AppConfig, GatewayMessage } from './types';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\nimport { classify, score } from './clients/v8Client';\n\nexport class MessageHandler {\n  constructor(\n    private apiClient: ApiClient,\n    private queue: MessageQueue | null,\n    private config: AppConfig,\n    private gatewayClient: GatewayClient\n  ) {}\n\n  async handle(msgData: any): Promise<void> {\n    const text = msgData[this.config.behavior.messageField];\n    if (!text || typeof text !== 'string') {\n      getLogger().debug({ msgData }, 'Message missing text field, skipping');\n      return;\n    }\n    getLogger().info({ text }, 'Processing message');\n    const startTime = Date.now();\n\n    // 使用 v8Client 调用 3104 分类和 3103 评分\n    let scene = 'default';\n    let isTask = false;\n    let scoreValue: number | string = 'N/A';\n    let scoringStrategy = 'DIRECT';\n\n    try {\n      // 1. 场景分类 (3104)\n      const classification = await classify(text);\n      scene = classification.scene;\n      isTask = classification.isTask;\n\n      // 2. 评分 (3103) - 仅对任务类型\n      if (isTask) {\n        const scoring = await score(text, {});\n        scoreValue = scoring.score;\n        scoringStrategy = scoring.recommendedStrategy;\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      getLogger().error({ err, text }, 'Failed to call v8 classification/scoring APIs');\n    }\n\n    const duration = Date.now() - startTime;\n    getLogger().info({ text, scene, isTask, score: scoreValue, strategy: scoringStrategy, duration }, 'Analysis complete');\n\n    if (this.config.reply.enabled && this.gatewayClient.isConnected()) {\n      let reply = this.config.reply.template || '';\n      reply = reply.replace('{{intent}}', scene).replace('{{score}}', String(scoreValue));\n      this.gatewayClient.send({ type: 'reply', content: reply });\n    }\n  }\n\n  async replayQueuedMessages(): Promise<void> {\n    if (!this.queue) return;\n    const messages = await this.queue.peek(20);\n    if (messages.length === 0) return;\n    getLogger().info({ count: messages.length }, 'Replaying queued messages');\n    for (const msg of messages) {\n      try {\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(msg.rawMessage) as GatewayMessage;\n        await this.handle(parsed.data || parsed);\n        await this.queue.dequeue(msg.id);\n      } catch (err) {\n        getLogger().error({ err, msgId: msg.id }, 'Failed to replay message, keeping in queue');\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776344146639}}
{"type":"message","id":"2532ed81","parentId":"1cbaec1e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:55:52.733Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message handler looks straightforward. The issue might be in how the webchat control UI sends messages to the gateway. Let me look at the gatewayClient and main.ts to understand the connection flow.\n\nActually, thinking about this more - the user said \"我的信息需要时间才会显示在屏幕上\". This could be a UI-side issue where the webchat control UI batches messages before sending them to the gateway. Or it could be a websocket/long-poll issue on the receiving end.\n\nLet me check the gatewayClient.ts to understand the connection mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"2babe9004a8c7e41ab8224f1b36a0f74935334db5af7a1035027f29f6fc425e4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2e46fe45c9b146a086c6b300","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/openclaw-listener/src/gatewayClient.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":680,"output":146,"cacheRead":46464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47290,"cost":{"input":0.000204,"output":0.0001752,"cacheRead":0.0027878399999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00316704}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344146718,"responseId":"06300f527f8c6113c7d70fac2ca5b258"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4fd09bca","parentId":"2532ed81","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:55:53.038Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2e46fe45c9b146a086c6b300","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import WebSocket from 'ws';\nimport { EventEmitter } from 'events';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\nimport { GatewayConfig } from './types';\n\nexport class GatewayClient extends EventEmitter {\n  private ws: WebSocket | null = null;\n  private reconnectTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n  private reconnectAttempts = 0;\n  private heartbeatTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n  private isManualClose = false;\n\n  constructor(private config: GatewayConfig) {\n    super();\n  }\n\n  public isConnected(): boolean {\n    return this.ws !== null && this.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN;\n  }\n\n  public getReconnectAttempts(): number {\n    return this.reconnectAttempts;\n  }\n\n  public connect(): void {\n    if (this.isManualClose) return;\n    const wsUrl = `${this.config.url}?token=${encodeURIComponent(this.config.token)}`;\n    getLogger().info({ url: wsUrl.replace(/token=.*/, 'token=***') }, 'Connecting to Gateway');\n    this.ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl, { handshakeTimeout: 10000, maxPayload: 10 * 1024 * 1024 });\n    this.ws.on('open', this.onOpen.bind(this));\n    this.ws.on('message', (data) => this.emit('message', data));\n    this.ws.on('error', (err) => this.emit('error', err));\n    this.ws.on('close', this.onClose.bind(this));\n    this.ws.on('pong', () => getLogger().trace('Received pong'));\n  }\n\n  private onOpen(): void {\n    getLogger().info('WebSocket connected');\n    this.reconnectAttempts = 0;\n    this.emit('open');\n    this.startHeartbeat();\n  }\n\n  private startHeartbeat(): void {\n    if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n    this.heartbeatTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      if (this.ws?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n        this.ws.ping();\n      }\n    }, this.config.heartbeatInterval);\n  }\n\n  private onClose(code: number, reason: Buffer): void {\n    getLogger().warn({ code, reason: reason.toString() }, 'WebSocket closed');\n    this.emit('close', code, reason);\n    if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n    if (!this.isManualClose) {\n      this.scheduleReconnect();\n    }\n  }\n\n  private scheduleReconnect(): void {\n    if (this.reconnectTimer) return;\n    const delay = Math.min(\n      this.config.reconnect.initialDelay * Math.pow(this.config.reconnect.factor, this.reconnectAttempts),\n      this.config.reconnect.maxDelay\n    );\n    this.reconnectAttempts++;\n    getLogger().info({ delay, attempt: this.reconnectAttempts }, 'Scheduling reconnect');\n    this.reconnectTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n      this.reconnectTimer = null;\n      this.connect();\n    }, delay);\n  }\n\n  public send(data: any): void {\n    if (this.ws?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n      this.ws.send(JSON.stringify(data));\n    } else {\n      getLogger().warn('Cannot send, WebSocket not open');\n    }\n  }\n\n  public close(): void {\n    this.isManualClose = true;\n    if (this.reconnectTimer) clearTimeout(this.reconnectTimer);\n    if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n    if (this.ws) {\n      this.ws.close(1000, 'Manual shutdown');\n      this.ws = null;\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776344152981}}
{"type":"message","id":"71a4c692","parentId":"4fd09bca","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:56:07.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the listener is a separate process that connects to the gateway via WebSocket and receives messages. It has its own v8Client that calls 3104/3103.\n\nBut this is the listener, not the webchat channel itself. The webchat channel is part of the gateway.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user's messages come in through the webchat channel → gateway → agent. The agent processes and replies. The reply goes back through gateway → webchat channel → user's UI.\n\nThe \"发送端延迟\" (message sending delay) could be:\n1. The user's message taking time to travel from their browser to the gateway\n2. The gateway processing and forwarding to the agent\n3. The agent processing\n\n\n4. The reply traveling back\n\nSince the gateway is WebSocket-based and the Control UI is HTTP-based, there's likely a polling mechanism bridging them. The real question is whether the bottleneck is in the gateway's message handling, the Control UI's polling interval, or something in between.\n\nLooking at the architecture: the Control UI sends messages via HTTP to the gateway, which then forwards them to the agent over WebSocket. The agent processes these and sends responses back through the same path. The delay could be happening at any of these hops. I'm trying to pinpoint whether this is a recent regression or a pre-existing condition, and if it's specifically tied to the Control UI channel or affecting other channels too. The user confirmed the delay started after the 4.14 update, so I need to focus on what changed in that release that could affect the webchat channel's message handling.\n\nThe most likely culprit is the SOUL.md restructuring or bootstrap changes. When the session initializes, if those files are being loaded or processed differently, it could create a bottleneck on the first message. I should also check the config-health.json to see if there's a performance degradation hint there.","thinkingSignature":"929bb6be351034b2a0e2389cd2d30705a4713364eb20ab266c1b9ced18ed9f44"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n这个是 listener，不直接管 webchat 延迟。让我换个方向——直接看 webchat 渠道的 channel 配置和健康状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_311da5b633fd4086a429ce6c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/logs/config-health.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f4ef4651097a45fd8b02b0fb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"channel*\" -o -name \"webchat*\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | grep -v \".git\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":853,"output":502,"cacheRead":47104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48459,"cost":{"input":0.0002559,"output":0.0006024,"cacheRead":0.00282624,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00368454}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344153039,"responseId":"06300f58aaff80aac7584c721e20f316"}}
