{"type":"message","id":"2bef6fbd","parentId":"d19575c4","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:56:14.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config-health.json shows that the openclaw.json config was last good at 20:35 today. The config is being monitored and hasn't shown any issues.\n\nLet me look at the actual webchat channel implementation. Since there's no webchat-specific extension here, the webchat channel is likely built into the gateway itself. Let me check the gateway's channel configuration.\n\nActually, wait - I should think about this differently. The user is using the OpenClaw Control UI (webchat). This UI connects to the gateway via WebSocket. Messages from the user go through the webchat channel to the gateway, and responses go back the same way.\n\nThe delay could be:\n1. The Control UI's polling interval for new messages\n\n\n2. The gateway's processing time before sending to the agent\n3. The gateway's polling for agent responses\n\nLet me check if there's a channel configuration in the openclaw.json or if there's any way to see what the webchat channel's message polling interval is set to.","thinkingSignature":"47d4976105d5b3dc7941d394f864df5d266fe852f5ecb21054695a223d95f0e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_688630feaa7c42eb874fee97","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":388,"output":243,"cacheRead":47936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48567,"cost":{"input":0.0001164,"output":0.0002916,"cacheRead":0.0028761599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0032841599999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344167733,"responseId":"06300f66584b3d1b3835dc24f642b750"}}
