{"type":"message","id":"6b1f3a3e","parentId":"b7dba03e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:57:42.770Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no Active Memory plugin enabled. That's good - ruled that out.\n\nLet me look at the Control UI channel implementation since the issue is specifically about the webchat channel and slow updates. The Control UI uses SSE (Server-Sent Events) or WebSocket to push messages to the client. If something changed in how the gateway pushes to the Control UI, that could explain the delay.\n\nActually, let me step back and think about what could have changed in 4.14:\n\n1. The markdown-it change shouldn't affect message delivery latency\n2. The context engine compaction changes could affect processing time\n3. The gateway/sessions change about heartbeat/cron events not overwriting shared-session metadata - this might affect how messages are routed\n\n\n4. The marked.js → markdown-it swap in the Control UI wouldn't cause upstream delays\n\nThe user says their sent messages take time to appear on screen. Looking at the Control UI webchat implementation, it likely sends messages via WebSocket to the gateway, which then routes them to the agent. The gateway processes the message and the agent responds, with the response sent back through the same channel. The delay could be in the message reaching the gateway, the gateway processing it, or the response coming back. I should check the Control UI's polling mechanism to understand the message flow better.\n\nThe changelog mentions \"compact engine-owned sessions from the first tool-loop delta\" - this is relevant because if the context engine is compacting messages as they arrive, it would add overhead on each message receipt. But the user reported slow responses across all messages after 4.14, not just during tool loops, so this might not be the main culprit. I need to focus on what changed specifically in the webchat channel or gateway message handling that could cause this delay.","thinkingSignature":"b1f6bbfdd8093008af8f6438b6cd02792d65aea633ccf8107f5db30157317721"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nActive Memory 没开，不是它。\n\n4.14 里 gateway/sessions 的改动比较可疑——`stop heartbeat, cron-event, and exec-event turns from overwriting shared-session routing and origin metadata`。但这个是防止元数据污染，不直接影响速度。\n\n真正影响 webchat 响应速度的更可能是 context engine 的这个改动：\n> \"compact engine-owned sessions from the first tool-loop delta\"\n\n如果这个 compact 逻辑在 4.14 之后被提前触发或者每次 turn 都触发，每条消息进来都要做压缩，会明显变慢。\n\n验证方法：看当前 session 的消息数量和 token 使用情况。`totalTokens: 24860` 不高，context 也没满。\n\n你说是\"我发出去的信息需要时间才会显示\"——这更像是 **发送端 UI 层的延迟**，不是 gateway 处理慢。能截个屏或者描述一下，你按发送键之后，过了多久那条消息才出现在聊天窗口里？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":767,"output":554,"cacheRead":59456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60777,"cost":{"input":0.00023009999999999998,"output":0.0006648,"cacheRead":0.00356736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00446226}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776344244896,"responseId":"06300fb4d7b4fefef09761a2deea799a"}}
