{"type":"message","id":"0d7dd44a","parentId":"76734c92","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:59:01.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is listening on port 3100 (and 3102). Let me try to get the session status from the gateway's API.\n\nWait, the gateway API returns 404. Let me check what API endpoints it has. Looking at the listener code, it connects to the gateway via WebSocket with a token. Let me look at the gateway's API endpoints more carefully.\n\nActually, let me look at the openclaw-listener's gatewayClient to understand how it communicates. The listener is at PID 577. It connects to the gateway via WebSocket. The gateway is at PID 503055.\n\nLet me check if there's a gateway status endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"af7559b5b005b066dc0a3cb8ea0f5f8a995f53095026cd32652e8a1c6a2d8e3a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f39eaf080b21473eb37a33d1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('gateway',{}).get('auth',{}).get('token',''))\" 2>/dev/null); curl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" http://localhost:3100/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_79e0ec9c80804dafaaa57c23","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3100/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":315,"output":275,"cacheRead":60736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61326,"cost":{"input":0.00009449999999999999,"output":0.00033,"cacheRead":0.0036441599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00406866}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344332314,"responseId":"0630100b20e0245755af9fc67a840460"}}
