{"type":"message","id":"5e386fc4","parentId":"d1f907de","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:00:07.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about the webchat polling mechanism differently. Since the Control UI is a web app served by the gateway on port 3100, it likely uses Server-Sent Events (SSE) or WebSocket for real-time communication. The messages you send go through the gateway via WebSocket, and the gateway processes them and pushes responses back.\n\nThe \"5 seconds to 1 minute\" delay is very suspicious. If it were a simple polling interval issue, the delay would be more consistent. The fact that sometimes it's 5 seconds and sometimes 1 minute suggests:\n\n1. The gateway's WebSocket is getting backlogged\n2. Some messages are triggering heavy processing that blocks the queue\n\n\n3. There's a queueing mechanism that processes messages sequentially, and heavier requests like the `/new` command take much longer to process\n\nI should check if the Control UI is using SSE or WebSocket connections. Looking at the Control UI files, I need to understand how it's actually receiving messages from the gateway.","thinkingSignature":"b47a3b49079a74919a17a1461c7460e8b6b1ac69c0d9fb340a9f6cba2d790d71"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nControl UI (port 3100) 是个静态 web 应用，它通过 WebSocket 或 SSE 跟 gateway 通信。让我看看它的客户端代码：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_05ff534d819840a9924e6f24","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist -name \"*.js\" | xargs grep -l \"EventSource\\|WebSocket\\|SSE\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f7856c38ff9445c0a1aa26cb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist -name \"*.html\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1143,"output":367,"cacheRead":62464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63974,"cos