{"type":"message","id":"25cda85b","parentId":"a1fba31c","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:02:49.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Control UI on port 3100 is a static HTML page served by the openclaw-gateway process (PID 503055). The Control UI is a web app that connects to the gateway via WebSocket.\n\nThe key question is: does the Control UI use polling or WebSocket? Since the gateway is on the same machine and there's a WebSocket connection, it should be real-time. But if the WebSocket connection is having issues, it might fall back to polling.\n\nThe delay pattern (5 seconds to 1 minute) is interesting. This could be:\n1. WebSocket reconnect delay - if the WS connection drops, it might take time to reconnect\n\n\n2. The gateway might be busy processing something and not immediately handling messages\n3. There could be a queue forming upstream from the Control UI\n\nI think the problem is actually in the Control UI's communication layer. When the user sends a message, it goes through the browser to the gateway's WebSocket connection. If that connection isn't healthy or there's congestion, messages could be buffering or delayed. And the reverse path—responses going back through the gateway to the Control UI—could also be affected by the same bottleneck.\n\nLet me check the gateway process itself. It's using 13.1% CPU and 620MB of memory, which is elevated. Looking at the CHANGELOG for 4.14, there's a fix about heartbeat and cron-event turns not overwriting shared-session routing and origin metadata. That suggests session state management changed, which could be causing the gateway to process messages differently or slower. There's also a change to how compact engine-owned sessions are handled from the first tool-loop delta.\n\nBut the user mentioned the delay is on the sending side—they're seeing 5 seconds to 1 minute before their message even appears in the chat window. That's a UI rendering issue, not a backend processing problem. The message might be getting queued in the Control UI before it's sent to the gateway, or there's something in the UI layer itself causing the delay.\n\nLooking at the 4.14 changelog, there was a fix for the Control UI/chat that replaced marked.js with markdown-it to prevent ReDoS attacks. This could have subtly changed how message rendering and queuing works in the UI, which would explain why messages are taking so long to appear after sending.\n\nI should ask whether the delay happens consistently with every message or just specific ones—text versus commands like /new—and whether the response time from the agent has also degraded.","thinkingSignature":"7e5a272ca17ecf2175a7d4d81842fa914421a2d85c332b206e7436e8dd4256e5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nControl UI 是静态 web 应用，通过 WebSocket 和 gateway (3102) 通信，理论上应该是实时的。5秒到1分钟的延迟说明 WebSocket 推送可能有问题。\n\n让我看看 gateway 的 WebSocket 连接状态和 session 队列：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2fcb2c7cdc7845a0b663a3bf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3102/api/sessions 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1201ae9fa4fe465a81625719","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('gateway',{}).get('auth',{}).get('token','NO_TOKEN'))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":257,"output":665,"cacheRead":66240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67162,"cost":{"input":0.00007709999999999999,"output":0.000798,"cacheRead":0.0039743999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0048495}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344542370,"responseId":"063010dc0f8a95e317eb1fc8bbe6f4c4"}}
