{"type":"message","id":"6761dd0f","parentId":"e3362852","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:03:23.306Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both 3100 and 3102 are serving the Control UI HTML (the same content). This is unusual - typically 3100 is the gateway API and 3102 serves the UI. \n\nLet me check what the gateway process is actually serving. Both ports returning the same HTML suggests that maybe the Control UI is served by the gateway itself on both ports, or there's a reverse proxy setup.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - 3102 has an API endpoint `/rpc` that returned the UI HTML when it expected something else. So 3100 and 3102 are both serving the Control UI static files.\n\nLet me check what ports the gateway is actually listening on and what services are running.\n\nThe real issue the user is experiencing seems to be with the Control UI itself displaying messages slowly, not the underlying gateway processing. Since both ports serve the same UI, the WebSocket connection for real-time updates would be handled through the gateway.\n\nWait - let me reconsider. The user's description \"发出的信息需要时间才会显示在屏幕上\" could mean:\n\n\n1. The message hasn't appeared in the UI yet (UI polling/fetching issue)\n2. The message was sent to the gateway but the UI hasn't received it yet (WebSocket push issue)\n\nSince the Control UI uses WebSocket for real-time updates, if the WebSocket connection has issues, messages would delay. But 5 seconds to 1 minute is a very wide range - if it were a polling interval issue, it would be more consistent.\n\nLet me think about what could cause variable delays in WebSocket message delivery:\n1. Network issues between Control UI and gateway\n2. Gateway processing queue backing up\n3. The WebSocket connection is actually falling back to HTTP long-polling due to some issue\n4. The Control UI's JavaScript is debouncing or batching messages incorrectly\n\nLooking at the changelog, there's a fix about WebSocket tick broadcasts being dropped for slow or backpressured clients causing disconnections with \"tick timeout\" - this could be relevant if the connection keeps getting dropped and re-established. But that's marked as fixed in an earlier version.\n\nI should check if the gateway has any active WebSocket connections and whether the Control UI is maintaining a persistent connection or falling back to polling. The user is on the OpenClaw Control UI surface, so I need to understand how that interface connects to the gateway and handles message delivery.","thinkingSignature":"bbf5c58f4a3dc7938b507d597851b169b1741d837e11b1cc92727a9ed3eebdec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7d63370e8e8647d081750a17","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep 3102; ss -tnp | grep 3102"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a5e0c52201fe4df098a8343f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3102/api/sessions 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":668,"output":566,"cacheRead":66688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67922,"cost":{"input":0.0002004,"output":0.0006791999999999999,"cacheRead":0.004001279999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004880879999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776344585274,"responseId":"06301108fb72bb2184ed7410a0b50c5c"}}
