{"type":"message","id":"8ddd9e07","parentId":"fabaf8e8","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:06:09.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"webchat 相关的代码不在这个 bundled 文件里。让我 search more specifically. The webchat channel is probably handled by the gateway differently. Let me look for how the gateway handles webchat inbound messages and outbound pushes.\n\nActually, let me step back. The user is using the Control UI (webchat) and experiencing delays. The Control UI is served on port 3100. It connects to the gateway on 3102 via WebSocket.\n\nBut I found earlier that the connection was IPv6 [::1]:3102 with RECEIVE-Q of 90 bytes. That's suspicious - if the control UI is connecting via IPv6 and the gateway is binding to both IPv4 and IPv6, there might be connection issues.\n \nLet me check the gateway's actual WebSocket implementation to see what's happening under the hood.","thinkingSignature":"9e2185e6412dd01a3deace9a401fcae3e981e2e16c54028173751db4d8346fbe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6e0c3a6092654598842a9a7f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"longpoll\\|long.*poll\\|pollInterval\" /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/*.js 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | grep -v \"qa-lab\\|matrix\\|discord\\|slack\\|telegram\\|feishu\\|whatsapp\\|signal\\|teams\" | grep -i \"webchat\\|control\\|3100\\|inbound\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ef29315bfbce48b4a212d44d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"inbound\\|messages.*fetch\\|pollMessages\" /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/*.js 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | grep -i \"webchat\\|control\\|3100\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":855,"output":376,"cacheRead":67264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68495,"cost":{"input":0.0002565,"output":0.00045119999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00403584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00474353999