{"type":"message","id":"557093dc","parentId":"6070790f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:06:28.084Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm not finding the webchat polling code in the bundled dist files. This suggests the Control UI's webchat implementation might be in the Control UI's own static files rather than in the gateway's bundled JS. Let me look for it in a different place.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully - the Control UI (port 3100) is a static web app. It might be a React app built separately. The webchat channel implementation might be in the openclaw-listener (PID 577) or somewhere else.\n\nWait, let me reconsider the architecture:\n- openclaw-gateway (PID 503055) - handles messaging routing\n- openclaw-listener (PID 577) - I saw this earlier, it's a separate process\n\n\n- Control UI (port 3100) - static web server\n\nThe listener I found earlier has a queue.ts file - maybe that's where the webchat implementation lives. The listener's messageHandler.ts was calling v8 classification and scoring, so that's not the webchat polling mechanism. The Control UI must be connecting to the gateway via WebSocket or HTTP to fetch messages, which would explain why the gateway's dist files show IPv6 connections.\n\nLooking at those ESTAB connections on port 3102, they could be from the Control UI connecting via WebSocket. Rather than continuing to trace through the code, I should take a more practical approach and measure the actual latency between when a message is sent and when it appears.","thinkingSignature":"61325eb91f7181320db83aa321ee9cb0fa905df684c5a72cddcc22e3a3fc9c21"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找不到 webchat 轮询代码的具体位置（可能在 UI 打包文件里）。换个思路——直接测实际延迟：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d970d6fc4e7942ea961f2df6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看 gateway 当前连接状态和消息队列\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer 0da4fe1cb845fc8386105026ee6b941b288a2a4264a"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_71ab087f62ea4c0ea54574bf","name":