{"type":"message","id":"3a19a9ab","parentId":"5c281d8f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:06:57.256Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is serving the Control UI as static HTML on port 3102, but it's not exposing an API at `/api/`. That means the UI's API calls go through the same WebSocket connection. This is a WebSocket-based architecture, not HTTP polling.\n\nThe Control UI connects to the gateway via WebSocket at `ws://localhost:3102`. But we already confirmed the WebSocket connections look normal in `ss` output.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user says messages take 5s to 1min to appear on screen. The Control UI is web-based. The browser receives messages via WebSocket from the gateway.\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that the Control UI's WebSocket connection is going through the WSL network stack since it's running on WSL. Let me check the WSL IP and whether there's some network latency issue.\n\n\nActually, I should reconsider what the user described - they said messages appear 5 seconds to 1 minute after sending. That's the message display delay on the sending side, which suggests the Control UI might not be receiving WebSocket messages in real time and could be falling back to HTTP polling instead. But I couldn't find evidence of that. Let me check if there's a separate webchat channel or if the Control UI itself has a polling mechanism I missed.","thinkingSignature":"95efd6938b67e6e0985efbe0be2cb0d95ff036ccff8d7c7bf7e9f89f451fc8bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f99cfc53bb8e4224a35f255c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"3000\\|3100\\|3101\\|3102\\|fetchMessages\\|getMessages\\|pollMessages\" /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/control-ui*.js 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2e671669d77246fc89cea6c7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist -name \"control-ui*.js\" 